.TH "snd_pcm_hw_param_max" 9 "snd_pcm_hw_param_max" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_pcm_hw_param_max \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_pcm_hw_param_max
.BI "(struct snd_pcm_substream *pcm "  ","
.BI "struct snd_pcm_hw_params *params "  ","
.BI "snd_pcm_hw_param_t var "  ","
.BI "unsigned int val "  ","
.BI "int *dir "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pcm" 12
PCM instance
.IP "params" 12
the hw_params instance
.IP "var" 12
parameter to retrieve
.IP "val" 12
maximal value
.IP "dir" 12
pointer to the direction (-1,0,1) or NULL
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Inside configuration space defined by PARAMS remove from PAR all 
values >= VAL + 1. Reduce configuration space accordingly.
Return new maximum or -EINVAL if the configuration space is empty
